SIMPLE: drained
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: drained
<hw>drained</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>having lost much energy or emotion
from vigorous activity; -- of people; <as>as, the day's events left her
completely <ex>drained</ex> of strength</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having resources completely depleted.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> depleted.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>having no power remaining; -- of a
battery.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> run-down.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>to go down the drain</b></col> <sn>1.</sn> <cd>to be
consumed in profitless activity; to be wasted; to become worthless.</cd>
<sn>2.</sn> <cd>to vanish or cease existing.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drainer</ent>⟦br⟧
